Difference Between Compilers and Interpreters.

1)Compilers compiles the entire code in one go. 
While interpreters takes single line of code at a time.

2)Compilers generates intermediate machine code.
While interpreters don't generate any machine code.

3)Compilers require more memory. 
While interpreters require less memory.

4)Compilers shows all the errors at once after compilation of entire program.
While interpreters display all the errors line by line.

5)Compilers are used by c,c++,c# etc. lanuages. 
While interpreters are used by java,PHP, python, Ruby.
